<HR> <P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00132200000000000000> Rotate Operation</A></H2>
<P>
	<A NAME=es5-xrot HREF="es5-xrotbig.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="" SRC="es5-xrot.gif"></A>
	<A HREF="es5-xrotbig.gif">Figure (es5-xrot): ARB5 Solid Edit Rotation about X</A>
<P>
<tt>mged&gt; <em>Select the ``Rotate'' entry in the solid edit menu</em> <BR>mged&gt; <em>p 45 0 0</em> <BR>mged&gt; 
</tt>
<P>
	<A HREF="es5-xrotbig.gif">Figure (es5-xrot)</A>
 shows a rotation of 45 degrees
about an axis parallel to the X axis.  
The rotate command is entered in the form <em>p a b c</em>
where <em>a</em>, <em>b</em>, and <em>c</em> are the angles
(in degrees) of rotation about the x, y, and z axes and intersect at point 1.
All rotation takes place about point 1.
<P>
<tt>mged&gt; <em>p 0 0 0</em> <BR>mged&gt; 
</tt>
<P>
This restores the original orientation of the solid.
<P>
